explanation: This solution uses a two-pointer approach to check if the substring from index i to i+total_len is equal to the concatenation of words. If it is, it adds i to the result list. Then it checks each word in the substring to see if it matches the corresponding word in words. If it does, it continues to the next word. If it doesn't, it breaks the loop and moves on to the next substring.

